<Author>LSBandKDF
<Content>Thank Goodness for the Melia Barcelona We booked a suite at the Melia Barcelona truely at the last minute on one of the last minute hotel websites. We arrived in Barcelona on the Saturday after Christmas to find that our apartment had been double booked. After staying in a lousy apartment we hit an internet cafe on Sunday morning and found a suite for my family of four and checked in by 1:00 that afternoon. They turned our almost disasterous holiday into a great week. The front desk team was so nice and made us feel welcome as soon as we walked in the door. As a previous review stated almost everyone except the maids spoke decent English. We spent a lot of evenings in the bar waiting for resturants to open for dinner and we were treated like family. It seemed like Delta crews use this hotel as well as other business people however because we were there over the holidays there were lots of families with young children. I don't think it is typically a family hotel but they were very good with our children even the 6 year old that kept breaking glasses in the bar.The concierge gave good resturant recommendations and even got us into a place for dinner on New Year's day when a lot of places were closed. Saved us wondering around the city looking at closed resturants.I did have a massage which was strickly OK. One complaint I have about the spa is that the massage rooms are right next to the weight room and the pool so I listened to kids playing in the pool and the sound of weights being clanged around during the massage.We ate at the hotel only on New Year's Eve and the food was suberb. They actually provided us with a kids dinner that was only about a quarter of the price of the adult meal. The internet was expensive - 鈧?2 per day. The location is about a 鈧? taxi ride to the Placa de Catalyuna and does have a good selection of resturants nearby. I was even able to find a butcher across the street and brought back some of Spain's famous ham. They shrink wrapped it for me.If you go to Barcelona and don't mind not staying in the city center - give the Melia Barcelona a look. 
