<Content>pleasant stay, some small minuses I stayed at a hotel as i was attending a conference at the same hotel. In general the hotel was nice and clean, and with a wonderful breakfast buffet, not to mention the perfect freshly squeezed orange juice. I was staying on the 20th floor, and i could see the sea from my window (if you ignored the not-so-nice building which blocked part of the view). the room was quite small though - it was good for me alone but i am guessing that sometimes it is rented as a double, but for 2 it would be too small. But i know that other rooms were bigger, so i would not worry about this too much.What i appreciated the most was the sound-proof window. Really, hardly any noise came in and my sleep was perfect. The air conditioning was also working, but i could not really figure out how exactly it works at frst. what i was disappointed in was that breakfast staff did not speak english at all. I was looking for milk for my coffee but could not find it so i asked one of the waitresses. she was showing me this and that until i remembered the spanish word and only then she gave me that milk. Also, i was not 100% sure that the front desk understood all i asked them.Also, there was not stationary PC with internet available. I guess that most guests come with laptops and wireless was available, but what if i do not have laptop with me but i do need internet? apart from that, i am happy with my stay, the subway was nearby, the hotel was good (as far as room and breakfast is concerned), the neighbourhood ok, and i do not exclude the possibility of staying there again. 
