<Content>Nothing special The Melia claims to be a 5* hotel but falls short by some way. It has few facilities and the rooms are comfortable but nothing special. The staff are friendly and helpful but not very efficient. My early morning wake up call (at 5.15am for an early flight to the UK) never came, and the excuse was that the automatic system had broken down - but there appeared to be no back up. My complaint was met with a shrug of the shoulders. Location is out of the centre but convenient for buses to all directions. The nearest Metro is about 10 minutes walk. I would not stay there by choice again. 
